
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `gst-tester-1.0` yek barname ast baraye test kardane element-ha va pipeline-haye GStreamer.  GStreamer yek framework baraye sakhtane application-haye multimedia mesle video player-ha va editor-haye video ast. Ba `gst-tester-1.0`, mitoonid element-ha va pipeline-haye GStreamer ro test konid ta az dorost kar kardan-e oonha motmaen beshid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Namayeshe rahnamaye dastoor va gozine-haye mojood.
    🔹 `--version`  --> ℹ️ Namayeshe version-e `gst-tester-1.0`.
    🔹 `<test-case>` --> 🧪 Esme test-case-i ke mikhayid ejra konid. Test case-ha obiatan file-haye python hastand.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ gst-tester-1.0 --help

    🔹 Namayeshe rahnamaye dastoor.

    $ gst-tester-1.0 my_test.py

    🔹 Ejdraye test-case `my_test.py`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ gst-tester-1.0 my_test.py

    🔹 Agar `my_test.py` yek test-case dorost baraye GStreamer bashad, ejra mishavad va natije-ye test namayesh dade mishavad. Agar test khata dashte bashad, peyghame khata namayesh dade mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `gst-tester-1.0` command is a program for testing GStreamer elements and pipelines. GStreamer is a framework for building multimedia applications like video players and video editors. With `gst-tester-1.0`, you can test GStreamer elements and pipelines to ensure they are working correctly.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--help`  --> ❓ Display the command's help message and available options.
    🔹 `--version`  --> ℹ️ Display the version of `gst-tester-1.0`.
    🔹 `<test-case>` --> 🧪 The name of the test case to execute. Test cases are usually Python files.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ gst-tester-1.0 --help

    🔹 Display the command's help message.

    $ gst-tester-1.0 my_test.py

    🔹 Execute the test case `my_test.py`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ gst-tester-1.0 my_test.py

    🔹 If `my_test.py` is a valid GStreamer test case, it will be executed, and the test result will be displayed. If the test fails, an error message will be shown.
